column3:
<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Tempatriq is in a mindmuddle.
Collect a piece of poxyleaf waterweed.
Collect a piece of fancyleaf waterweed.
Collect a piece of gaudyleaf waterweed.
Return the waterweed samples to Tempatriq.
Oh, what is Tempatriq to do? It is so near, and yet so far...
Earlend Tempatriq, lowlander! She told potsworn friend about the beautiful waterweed of Marsh Ligaka, and potsworn friend says she wants to study it closeeyes.

But waterweed grows at the bottom of the water, and Tempatriq can't fishwalk. Can't ask potsworn to collect it herself, either─it would go against the potpact. You wouldn't happen to be a talented fishwalker, would you?
...You're a talented fish<Emphasis>breather</Emphasis>, too!? Then you are the perfect lowlander for the job!
Need to gather three types of waterweed from Marsh Ligaka: poxyleaf is pink and poisonlooking, fancyleaf is lacy and lovely, and gaudyleaf is super shimmershiny! Please find them for Tempatriq!
Many kinds of waterweed grow in Marsh Ligaka. Tempatriq only needs you to collect three of the most distinctive: poxyleaf type, fancyleaf type, and gaudyleaf type.
Pfff... pfffkohhh... Did you find the waterweed?
Wonderdeeds! They're even more beautiful up close than they are in the water!
Tempatriq will show them to her potsworn friend right away! They're sure to give her plenty of mindfruit.

She is an expert at reproducing nature─not only in prettylooks, but in funnytraits, too. This waterweed has a very special funnytrait: it changes color depending on the warmth of the water in which it grows, its exposure to light, or even over the longyears.
If she can craft danglejewels that do the same, they will surely sell for a potload of jinglyshine!
